cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with drawings of graphs in the Euclidean and hyperbolic planes, and discusses properties of self-approaching and increasing-chord paths in these drawings.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper studies properties of triangulations, planar 3-trees, and binary cactuses, which are all objects of interest in discrete mathematics.
- cs.GT (Graph Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with properties of paths and connectivity in graphs.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses properties of paths in graphs, which can be relevant in network analysis.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the computational complexity of constructing self-approaching and increasing-chord drawings of trees and binary cactuses.
